  "prompt": "Can I put a sleep number matress on a platform frame?",
  "response": "Yes, you can put a Sleep Number mattress on a platform frame. However, there are a few considerations to keep in mind:\n\n1. **Support**: Ensure that the platform frame provides adequate support for the mattress. Sleep Number mattresses are designed to be used with a solid, flat surface or a proper adjustable base. If your platform frame has slats, they should be closely spaced (typically no more than 3 inches apart) to prevent sagging.\n\n2. **Height**: Consider the height of the platform frame, as it may affect how easy it is to get in and out of bed.\n\n3. **Warranty**: Check the mattress warranty information to ensure that using it on a platform frame won't void the warranty. \n\n4. **Comfort**: Test the mattress on the platform frame to ensure that it feels comfortable and provides the support you need.\n\nIf your platform frame meets these criteria, it should work well with your Sleep Number mattress.",
